message.content:
1. Eicosapentaenoic acid is an omega-3 polyunsaturated fatty acid.
2. Docosahexaenoic acid is an omega-3 polyunsaturated fatty acid.
3. Eicosapentaenoic acid and docosahexaenoic acid are functionally important.
4. Eicosapentaenoic acid and docosahexaenoic acid are the most important omega-3 polyunsaturated fatty acids.

messages.content:
Statement: Eicosapentaenoic acid (EPA) and docosahexaenoic acid (DHA) are functionally the most important omega-3 polyunsaturated fatty acids (PUFAs).
